tags: karamkalla paratha,Cabbage Stuffed Paratha Recipe,how to make cabbage paratha,Cabbage Paratha Recipe with Step By Step Photos,patta gobhi paratha recipe,cabbage paratha without stuffing,cabbage paratha punjabi style,‡§™‡§§‡•ç‡§§‡§æ‡§ó‡•ã‡§≠‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•ç‡§ü‡§´‡•ç‡§° ‡§™‡§∞‡§æ‡§Ç‡§†‡§æ ‡§∞‡•á‡§∏‡§ø‡§™‡•Ä,cabbage paratha recipe in hindi,How to make Patta Gobhi Paratha,cabbage paratha for toddler
description: Cabbage Paratha Recipe, patta gobhi paratha recipe, band gobhi paratha recipe, Karamkalla Paratha,Ingredients:Cabbage - 300 gmsWheat flour - 2 cups (300 gms)Oil - 3 to 4 tbspGreen Coriander - 2 to 3 tbsp (finely chopped)Green chillies - 2 (finely chopped)Ginger paste - ¬Ω tspCumin seeds - ¬º tspCoriander powder - ¬Ω tspRed chilli powder - ¬º tspSalt - less than 1 tsp How to make stuffed Cabbage Paratha For the dough 1- Take 2 cups of wheat flour and add ¬Ω tsp of salt in it. 2- Add 2 tsp of Oil in it and mix them. 3- Add 1 cup of water in intervals and knead the soft dough for parathas.4- Cover and set it for 15-20 minutes.For the stuffing 1- Take 300 gms of cabbage, remove its upper 3-4 leaves and separate the rest of them individually.2- Add salt in the lukewarm water in a vessel. 3- Dip the cabbage leaves in it for 10 minutes. 4- Drain them out and wash with fresh water in a strainer so that the extra water moves out of it. 5- Keep them in basket and dry them until water disappears.6- Make a bunch of some leaves and chop them finely. 7- Preheat 2 tsp of Oil in a pan, add 2 tsp of cumin seeds in it and roast on the low flame.8-  Saute ¬Ω tsp of Ginger paste, 2 finely chopped Green chillies, ¬Ω tsp of coriander powder, ¬º tsp of Red chilli powder in it.9- Add chopped cabbage in the roasted spices, ¬Ω tsp of salt, stir and cook them for 2 minutes. 10- Add 2 to 3 tbsp of finely chopped coriander and cook it while stirring for 1 to 2 minutes. 11- The stuffing is ready and has cooked. For the paratha 1- After, 20 minutes mash the dough slightly and preheat the pan or parathas. ‚Äò2- Take a dough lump and roll it to make a round ball. 3- Roll it in the dry flour and flatten it to the diameter of 6 to 7 inches.4- Spared some Oil in it and spread it evenly. 5- Place the stuffing over it and spread it thinly. 6- Fold it in a square shape from all the sides and spared some Oil over it. 7- Roll it in the dry flour and toss the extra flour. 8- Press it using your fingers from all the corners. 9- Flatten it using a rolling pin into the shape of a square. 10- Spread some Oil on the pan and place paratha over it to fry.11- Let it roast from the bottom and flip it later on.12- Cook it until light colour spots appears on it. 13- Adds some Oil in it and spread it. 14- Flip and fry by pressing them until they are golden. 15- Remove it and place on mini bowl over a plate. 16- Prepare all the parathas in the same way and serve. It requires a little planning i.e. soaking chana dal for about 2-3 hours at least. It tastes just awesome. Specially if you are bored of having same dal rice then this is a fantastic alternative. Do try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.Ingredients:‚Ä¢ 2 tsp Oil‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Mustard seeds‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seeds‚Ä¢ Dry red chilies‚Ä¢ Curry leaves‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup soaked Chana dal‚Ä¢ Red chili powder‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup Chana dal‚Ä¢ Salt to taste‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Tamarind juice (Optional)‚Ä¢ 2~3 cups cooked RiceMethod:‚Ä¢ Heat up oil in a pan. ‚Ä¢ Add mustard seeds and let them pop up.‚Ä¢ Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.‚Ä¢ Add dry red chilies, curry leaves, red chili powder and mix well.‚Ä¢ Wash and soak chana dal in enough water for about 2-3 hours.‚Ä¢ Add soaked chana dal, salt to taste and mix well.‚Ä¢ Cover and cook on medium heat until chala dal cooks nice and   soft for about 10 minutes.‚Ä¢ Add tamarind juice, coriander leaves and mix well. ‚Ä¢ Tamarind juice is optional. You can skip it if you want. ‚Ä¢ Take rice and add cooked chana dal in it.‚Ä¢ Mix everything carefully.
